a theory… kind of

so i don’t know if anyone has pointed this out yet considering i haven’t been active but they released this version of the new army bomb a few weeks ago:

the main difference in this version is that the bts logo is inside. which could potientally explain the E concept photos. maybe they aren’t bubbles or , as i called them, hamster balls. maybe they are army bombs. a symbol for how we keep them alive (the plants, flowers etc)? it’s just a thought i wrote up during lunch but it seems plausible.

bonus:

the army bombs are also featured i the epiphany mv in jins house. i don’t know yet what this means, maybe that we are always with them. so far every part of this comeback has featured ARMY in some way, maybe saying we are their answer.

summary: BTS Reactions - You give birth at home with no midwife When you and your husband finally work out that you’re in labour, it’s...
body:
BTS Reactions - You give birth at home with no midwife

When you and your husband finally work out that you’re in labour, it’s too late to move you to the hospital. At the beginning of the pregnancy, you’d discussed a home birth, but you never really went through with it. It seems like you’re going to get one anyway though, because your husband has no choice but to deliver the baby himself.

Jin

Jin tries his very best to remain as calm as he possibly can while rushing around to try and find some surgical gloves - he knows he has some hidden somewhere, and every second he wastes means you have to wait for his comfort and help. He really wishes there was another way to do this, but he’s really just going to have to square his shoulders and do his best to help you through it.

Jin’s feeling much more in control of himself when the baby’s born. He’s sure there’s some official bits to do, but that can wait. It wasn’t easy, but he can now sit down beside you with his precious baby boy, and fall in love with his little family. He’ll search up what to do next in a bit. Jin’s always liked to bask in the moment and drink in it’s beauty, and this will be his most treasured memory of them all.

Yoongi

Right now is probably one of Yoongi’s Top Ten Most Terrifying Moments, there’s an actual baby coming out of you any second, and he wants to hide away until it’s all over. Not that he’d ever let you see that. He acts with an aura of authority about him, telling you what to do with an absolute tone. It’ll put you at ease, which is good. Stress is bad for the baby,

“She’s so beautiful,” Yoongi coos much later on, when you’ve both struggled through the birth. The both of you are exhausted beyond belief, collapsed into each other while you cradle your baby girl. She’s cried a lot, but Yoongi knows that it’s not a bad sign. She has strong lungs, “You did really well making this,” Is the best compliment Yoongi’s mind can give him in that moment, but you appreciate it whole-heartedly. You snuggle into the trembling shoulder of your husband as his fingers gently trace her small features.

Hoseok

There are actual tears marring Hoseok’s vision. He always knew he was quite sensitive and easily scared, but he’s never truly hated it until right now. He does his absolute best to hide his fear from you, trying to speak to you confidently to put you at ease. To be fair, he does alright. You see straight through him, but the effort is important to you, even now. You just hope he’ll actually be able to help you through this birth,

“You did so well,” Hoseok praises you a while later, holding his daughter with both arms. He looks ecstatic, and you can tell that fatherhood definitely suits him. After the birth was over, he washed you hair for you, where you were lying. You were obviously exhausted, so while your daughter slept, he did his best to make you feel pretty and happy again. He’s now sat next to you, looking down at you and his daughter adoringly. You’ve never seen him so happy.

Namjoon

When you first mentioned a home birth, Namjoon had done hours and hours of research. He wanted to know exactly what you were going to be getting yourself into, and what he could do to help. The only issue is, there is nobody else here right now. There’s nobody to help you give birth other than him. It frightens Namjoon so much, but he knows that he’ll be able to do it. All that research will definitely have paid off after this.

After the birth, Namjoon is nearly as tired as you. Nearly. He’s about to make some calls to work out what to do now - there’s a matter of birth certificates and all of that. But that can wait a few minutes, since all he wants to do right now is kiss you, smothering you in his love until you’re crying with laughter. It’s not practical, since your baby boy is sleeping just a few feet away, but neither one of you minds. You’re so excited for the next chapter in your life.

Masterlist

body: I haven’t been hyping up or posting about BTS because theres already soooo many blogs and people doing so, that it feels repetitive. Plus I’ve been taking time off from them and hyping up my other groups that deserve love and also been with them since the beginning. And for some reason since BTS has become so mainstream now, I dont have that gushy feeling no more. Which makes me sad. But I loose interest on things that I love that start becoming trends for some reason. Not that I would drop BTS, but idk, I guess people killed it for me. But when hyping up my other groups I get that gushy feeling so idk lol🤷🏻‍♀️

summary:
Yoongi 「you ask him for help」
Trigger Warning; suicide attempt, blood

body:
Yoongi 「you ask him for help」

Trigger Warning; suicide attempt, blood

i really do not want this to be a post with a sad tone. i’m so sorry i couldn’t write this as soon as you requested it. But i hope you are okay, anonie. and this is to everyone, i am always open for talking.

You feel blood trickles down your wrist as you try to dial your boyfriend’s number on your phone. Min Yoongi, a man who has been there with you through ups and downs. Your life has been more than just a mess recently, and you do not want to bother Yoongi as you know he was also busy with all the comeback preparation too. You thought you are going to be okay on your own, but when the dark thought come knocking on your door like an old friend, when your body forces you to do something you know you would regret, you could just surrender. Those thoughts have always won.

“Yoongi,” you called from the other line, voice shaking.

“Y/n, are you okay?” You could hear his heavy breathing together with his concerned tone, maybe he has just done with the practice.

“Yoongi,” you called again, tears flowing down your cheeks. “It hurts.”

“What hurts? Y/n, tell me what hurts?”

“I don’t know, but it hurts. Can you come home now? Please, help me.”

“I’m going home now, okay. Stay with me, y/n.” Yoongi signals the boys to help him find his car keys. Jimin found it near Yoongi’s locker. He throws the keys to him and Yoongi quickly left, mouthing a ‘thank you.’ The rest of the boys donot know what have happened but they know for sure it is important, or else Yoongi won’t leave without saying anything.

“y/n, are you there? Hey, baby talk to me.”

“Yes, I’m here.”

“I’m in the car now. I’ll be home shortly, okay?”

“Okay.” You answer him, barely audible.

“y/n, do you hear me?”

“Yes, I do, Yoongi.” Yoongi could feel the weakness in your voice. He really wished the dorm is not that far from your place.

“Good, tell me about your day. Keep me updated, baby girl.”

“I ate toast and fried eggs this morning and I read the rest of the novel I bought last week and-“ you pause, your voice becoming softer and softer.

“And?”

“And, I remember I went to sleep.”

“What a day you have there.”

“Hell yes.” you chuckled.

“y/n?” you didn’t reply him.

“y/n love?”

“y/n, can you answer me?”

The number you are calling is temporarily disconnected.

“fuck, fuck.” Yoongi tried calling you back, but got nothing.

“y/n, please be okay. Please be okay. Please be okay.”

Yoongi rushed in the apartment as soon as he arrived. It is all dark and he turns on the light as he walks pass room by room, trying to find you.

“y/n!”

“y/n!”

You could hear Yoongi calling you but you donot have the power to answer him anymore. You tried to knock the bathtub to tell him you were there. When Yoongi opens the door and finds you lying against the bathtub with bloody wrist, he could only imagine what you’ve been through for you to come down to this.

“y/n.”

“Yoongi?”

“Hey love, I’m here already.”

“Yoongi?”

“Yes, yes, this is Yoongi.”

“Yoongi,” you hug him as hot liquids continue to wet your not-yet-dried cheek.

“Yes, y/n?”

“Yoongi.”

“Yes, y/n?” Yoongi hug you back, gently, afraid that you might break by his touch. When you calm down, Yoongi carried you to the bed. He cleans your cut and wraps it with gauze. When he found you, he could only hope that the cut is not too deep, turns out he was right.

Yoongi tucks you in and you quickly fall asleep. He continues cleaning the bathroom and cautiously keeps all razors out of your reach. He called Seokjin and asks him how did he cook his ultimate comfort food and cooks it for you. When he was done with basically everything, he went back to check you. Only until he saw your peaceful sleeping figure, that he realizes he really misses you.

“What happened to you, princess? Why do you do that to yourself.”

“Can we talk about that later?” you answer with your eyes close.

“Of course. I thought you are asleep.”

“I were.”

“Go back to sleep, silly.”

“I will.”

And there’s a long silence before Yoongi kisses you on your lips, short, but assuring.

“Thank you for calling me.”

“You sound like that operator.”

“I really do.” You opened your eyes and in the darkness, even though you could barely see it, you could see how tired he is.

“Why should you thank me because I call you? It’s supposed to be the other way around, isn’t it?”

“Let me re-phrase that. Thank you for asking me for help. Thank you that you think I could provide that help for you.”

“Why do you even doubt yourself?”

“Well, nevermind then.” You let out a weak laugh.

“Go to sleep too, sleepyhead. I can see your eyebags with my shitty eye-sight.”

“Someone can call me sleepyhead already.”

“Stop teasing me.” You replied as you close your eyes again, now, Yoongi too.

“Thank you, Yoongi.” you whispered. He didn’t answer but you know he heard you, loud and clear.

Thank you for coming back home to save me.

Thank you.
